{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", "id": "msg_01S29Pp87xWZWy4Ws94XjRjf", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I'm ready to help you explore and search through this codebase! I'm Claude Code, Anthropic's official CLI for Claude, and I specialize in file search and code analysis.\n\nHere's what I can do for you:\n\n- **Search files** using glob patterns to find specific files or file types\n- **Search code contents** using regex patterns to find text, function definitions, imports, etc.\n- **Read and analyze** specific files you're interested in\n- **Navigate the codebase** efficiently to understand its structure\n\nI'm operating in **read-only mode** - I can only view and analyze existing code, not modify it.\n\nThe current working directory is `/code` and this is a git repository on branch `branch_1`. The repo has a clean status with recent commits including work on `app.py` and some data additions.\n\nWhat would you like me to search for or explore in this codebase? Just let me know:\n- A specific file or file type you're looking for\n- Code patterns or functionality you want to understand\n- The structure or organization of the project\n- Anything else you'd like to investigate"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 761, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 249, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
