{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_011V82uv6wWJCXN4WkzYGWEs", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm ready to help you explore the codebase and design implementation plans.\n\nI'm currently in READ-ONLY mode, which means I can:\n- **Explore** the codebase using tools like Glob, Grep, and Read\n- **Analyze** existing code patterns and architecture\n- **Design** detailed implementation plans\n- **Use Bash** for read-only operations (ls, cat, git log, find, etc.)\n\nBut I **cannot**:\n- Create, modify, or delete any files\n- Run commands that change system state\n- Install packages or dependencies\n\nLet me get oriented by checking what's in this repository:\n\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">cd /code && ls -la</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">cd /code && find . -type f -name \"*.py\" -o -name \"*.js\" -o -name \"*.ts\" -o -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"*.md\" | head -20</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">cd /code && git log --oneline -10</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n\nI'm warmed up and ready! When you provide me with requirements and optionally a perspective, I'll:\n\n1. Thoroughly explore the relevant parts of the codebase\n2. Understand existing patterns and architecture\n3. Design a comprehensive implementation plan\n4. Identify the critical files needed for implementation\n\nWhat would you like me to help you design today?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 950, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 445, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"hello :)\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_015RTQ7BQmBtPDP5o4JvGHMF", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm Sculptor, an AI coding agent powered by Claude Code. I'm here to help you with coding tasks, bug fixes, and answering questions about your code.\n\nI can see you're working on `branch_1` with a clean git status. Your repository has some recent commits including \"Stuff\", \"app.py commit\", and \"add some cool data\".\n\nHow can I help you today? Feel free to ask me to:\n- Write or modify code\n- Fix bugs\n- Explain how code works\n- Explore your codebase\n- Create pull requests\n- Or anything else coding-related!"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3950, "cache_read_input_tokens": 14281, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 3950, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 137, "service_tier": "standard"}, "context_management": {"applied_edits": []}}}
